GROUPINFO

This program retrieves information from the UNIX GROUP database.

Synopsis:

$ groupinfo [{groupname|gid} [{-l|<query(s)>}]] [-q] [-V]

where:

<groupname>	a groupname to query on
-l		list users who have the specified group as default
<query(s)>	query keyword (listed below)
<gid>		a group ID to query
-q		do not print anything out (just return exit-code)
-V		print program version to standard-error and then exit

queries:

groupname	return the group name
gid		return the group ID
members		return the users within the group

